File: A University of KwaZulu-Natal student accused of murdering his roommate was sent for mental evaluation. JOHANNESBURG - A University of KwaZulu-Natal student accused of murdering his roommate is being sent to a psychiatric facility for mental evaluation. Khanyile Nzimande, (25), is accused of killing and setting Samkelo Zondi alight. Nzimande has allegedly claimed Zondi was a zombie and practised witchcraft. READ: UKZN student arrested for alleged murder of fellow student Family members of the deceased and UKZN students packed the court gallery. Nzimande abandoned his bail application. The matter is due back in court on 5 November.